{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsT6c6hEB8RbQoDb4TLd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are met. Summary:\n\n**Upgrade path taken**: 3.12.14 → 3.13.7 → 4.1.8 (stepping through 3.13 was mandatory — jumping straight to 4.1 failed at boot with `stream_filtering: required feature flag not enabled`, since that flag is introduced in 3.13 and is a hard prerequisite for 4.x).\n\n**Key engineering steps**:\n1. Discovered the `data` volume was `emptyDir`, which does not survive StatefulSet-triggered Pod recreation — migrated it to a `hostPath` volume (`/var/lib/rabbitmq-pv-data`) with per-pod isolation via `subPathExpr: $(POD_NAME)`, copying existing Mnesia data into place first (fixed an `.erlang.cookie` permission bug along the way — Erlang requires strict 400 perms).\n2. For each major-version jump, used the officially-supported **full cluster stop → swap image → start** method rather than a live rolling upgrade, avoiding any period where incompatible major versions coexist in the same cluster.\n3. Hit a second issue: `OrderedReady` pod management deadlocks a full cold-cluster-start (node 0 waits for Mnesia sync from nodes 1/2, which never start because node 0 isn't Ready yet). Recreated the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 nodes boot concurrently and can find each other.\n4. Enabled all RabbitMQ feature flags at each stage before upgrading further.\n\n**Final state**:\n- All 3 nodes report **RabbitMQ 4.1.8** (Erlang 27.3.4.14), cluster shows all 3 as Running Nodes.\n- `/app`, `/ops`, and `/` vhosts all present; `app-queue` still `classic` type with the `ha-all` policy attached, and message count preserved exactly through the version stop/start (264 messages before and after), now growing again (378) as producers resumed.\n- `app-client`, `app-producer`, and `ops-client` all recovered to `1/1 Running` after reconnecting.\n- All changes used only native Kubernetes resources (StatefulSet, Secret, ConfigMap, Pod) — no CRDs or operators."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1274,"cache_read_input_tokens":204831,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1274},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"afc25e59-58cb-4815-93ac-c59109c6fcbc","uuid":"c7fbedc8-8990-41c1-8188-9b0c3ab6cac0","request_id":"req_011CcsT6YxgAx4g9stcRmQSe"}
